  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>red&nbsp;onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/517.step1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/517.step1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/517.step1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/517.step1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/517.step1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong> over a low heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced&nbsp;onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> (to draw out the moisture) and cook for 10 min or until slightly softened and starting to brown</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>vegetable</strong>&nbsp;<strong>stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;in 350ml<span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;[700ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled water</strong>, stir in the <strong>meat free mince</strong>, then set aside</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/517.step2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/517.step2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/517.step2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/517.step2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/517.step2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span>&nbsp;<strong>butter</strong> to a pot over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once melted, add 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span><strong>&nbsp;flour</strong> and stir for 2-3 min or until a sandy&nbsp;paste has formed - this is your <strong>roux</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
